						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of Rāmaliṅga temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśivarāya, 1547-48 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1469, Plavaṅga, the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> being 10. The details are lost. The date corresponds approximately to 1547-48 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records the remission of taxes in favour of the barbers of Toṟagala-sīme by Rāmarāya and Veṅkaṭādri. Koṇḍōja and Sidōja of the community also received some concessions.</p>						

						</summary>
